cs.GT, cs.MA, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.NE 

This paper deals with game theory and optimization in the context of Markov Decision Processes (MDPs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Computer Science - Game Theory and Decision Science). The paper also involves multiple decision makers and congestion effects, which suggests the possibility of it being categorized under cs.MA (Computer Science - Multiagent Systems). The use of sensitivity analysis and implicit function type analysis suggests the possibility of it being categorized under cs.LG (Computer Science - Learning). The paper also deals with stochastic dynamics, which suggests the possibility of it being categorized under cs.SY (Computer Science - Systems and Control) or cs.NE (Computer Science - Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
